In this article, President Donald J. Trump proclaims June 14, 2018, as Flag Day and the week starting June 10, 2018, as National Flag Week. He emphasizes the significance of the American flag as a symbol of liberty and gratitude to service members and their families. The flag has been present during historic moments such as the homecoming of Americans released from captivity, moon missions, the battle of Iwo Jima, and the recovery operations after the September 11 attacks. Trump urges all Americans to observe Flag Day and National Flag Week by displaying the flag and honoring America's heritage.